    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nLSP jump operations such as `buf.definition`/`buf.type_definition` do not follow the `switchbuf` option. Their behavior is controlled by `vim.lsp.LocationOpts`, which, compared to the `vim.lsp.ListOpts` it inherits from, only adds a `reuse_win` key. When this key is `true`, the effect is very similar to `set switchbuf=useopen`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWe should follow the `switchbuf` option and drop `reusewin`. Considering that functions like `buf.definition` open the quickfix window when there are multiple results, and jumping between quickfix entries follows `switchbuf`, I believe this would be more intuitive.",
